flowRoot.flowPara: Screens are often one of the main consumers of power. You can reduce the amount of power used reducing screen brightness and "Dim screen when active" is on.
Wi-Fi uses power when data is transferred, and when looking for a network to connect to. To reduce Wi-Fi power usage, either turn it off or reduce network usage.
Bluetooth uses power when transferring data or looking for and pairing with devices. To reduce Bluetooth power usage, turn off Bluetooth.
System power consumption includes basic operations and usage.
Dotted line indicates periods when the device has been off on suspended, and the charge over time has been extrapolated from the data.
